  "body": "The current implementation has a bug that relies on shanghaiTime being configured which might not be the case for future devnets/testnets, e.g. if they start with cancunTime: 0 and don't configure shanghaiTime at all.\n\nhttps://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/4875ba3a64d9a438c452e5c855a6fe2f83d5f5d8/consensus/merge/src/main/java/org/hyperledger/besu/consensus/merge/MergeProtocolSchedule.java#L72-L75\n\nA better approach would be to use `config.getForkBlockTimestamps().stream().findFirst().isPresent()`",
